survey_response.review_text: Had a wonderful experience with the Doctor.She was really friendly and wasn't just filling in an appointment slot. Even before asking about the actual problem, she ensued that she knows about all other details about the child such as past problems, diet etc. Coming to the actual problem, she never was in a hurry to listen and prescribe. She listened to the problem and subsequent questions very patiently and answered all of them in detail. Whether the treatment works or not is secondary but the intent and content of the doctor matters and thats where she has been a wonderful person. In my experience with most doctors at Bangalore, they expect us to book another appointment in order to ask follow up questions. But Dr Tejaswini never had any such expectations. In fact when I booked another appointment after 4 days, she asked me why did I book another appointment. This was very kind and ethical of her and builds a trust that she will not prescribe any unnecessary treatments or tests etc.Coming to the actual treatment, Dr was really thorough and told me all stages of treatment. She didn't prescribe all tests etc for the first day itself and asked us to wait before getting tests and subsequent medications.Glad to have found her for my child.Thank you!

I am really happy with the treatment. Doctor will explain the issue very clearly and patiently repeats if we asked twice. Unnecessarily she will not go for antibiotics and all. I went for my baby (6 months old) who has very bad motions (diarrhoea), doctor has suggested diet plan to my baby and gave very mild medication and not rushed for antibiotics. Overall satisfied with the treatment and doctor. If you are looking for best Pediatrician for your baby, without doubt you can visit Dr. Tejaswini mam.

Although we just went for vaccination, doctor enquired about the kids daily routine and behavior, history of any illness, food phone habits etc.. Which was impressive. Any other centre would normally give the vaccine and move on to the next kid.
The way she talks may give the impression that she is in a hurry, but its just her way of talking. If visiting for the first time, please spend a few minutes more to adjust to her rate od speech or ask her again, she is really good and friendly!!, today was our 3rd visit.

most reliable doctor in Bangalore.

I had booked a video consultation on June 13th at 7.15pm. I was asked to wait until 8pm as she was busy. I waited but didn’t receive any call nor my calls were answered. Later at night ,over the message she confirmed she would connect the next day.
